# Revisit by: 2025-10-15
CVE-2025-47907

# CVE-2025-47906: Go os/exec.LookPath PATH environment variable handling vulnerability.
# Affects: yq (v1.22.4), tx (v1.16.15), gosu (v1.18.2) - all Go binaries
# Rationale: Low risk in our containerized environment with controlled PATH and no user input to LookPath.
# The affected binaries are system utilities used in controlled contexts, not user-facing components.
# Recent CVE (Sep 2025) - waiting for vendor updates to Go stdlib used in these binaries.
# Added: 2025-09-21
# Revisit by: 2025-11-15
CVE-2025-47906

# CVE-2025-47912, CVE-2025-58183, CVE-2025-58186, CVE-2025-58187, CVE-2025-58188, CVE-2025-61724
# Go stdlib vulnerabilities affecting third-party binaries (gh, tx, gosu)
# Affects: gh (Go v1.22.4), tx (Go v1.16.15), gosu (Go v1.18.2)
# Vulnerabilities:
#   - CVE-2025-47912: IPv6 Parse function permits non-IPv6 values (fixed in Go 1.24.8, 1.25.2)
#   - CVE-2025-58183: tar.Reader lacks max size limit on sparse file entries (fixed in Go 1.24.8, 1.25.2)
#   - CVE-2025-58186: HTTP header count limit bypass (fixed in Go 1.24.8, 1.25.2)
#   - CVE-2025-58187: Certificate name constraint checking performance issue (fixed in Go 1.24.9, 1.25.3)
#   - CVE-2025-58188: DSA public key validation excessive memory consumption (fixed in Go 1.24.8, 1.25.2)
#   - CVE-2025-61724: HTTP ReadResponse string concatenation memory issue (fixed in Go 1.24.8, 1.25.2)
# Rationale: These are CI/CD tools (gh, tx) and privilege escalation utility (gosu) used exclusively
#            in controlled containerized environments for build/deployment automation. They do not
#            process untrusted user input and are not exposed to external networks. The binaries are
#            vendor-supplied pre-compiled releases that we cannot rebuild. Actual exploitation risk
#            is minimal given the controlled usage context. Vendors (especially Transifex with Go 1.16.15
#            from 2022) are unlikely to release patched versions soon.
# Added: 2025-11-06
# Revalidated: 2026-02-17 (CI Trivy still reports embedded Go stdlib in vendor binaries)
# Revisit by: 2026-04-15 (check for updated vendor releases)
CVE-2025-47912
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-58186
CVE-2025-58187
CVE-2025-58188
CVE-2025-61724

